    walk: `Friend, today's verse calls us to a lasting joy and delight in our spouse, a rejoicing that continues through all the years: *Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.* God calls us, friend, to keep rejoicing in our spouse, to keep delighting in the one we married; let us walk in this today.

See the call to a blessed fountain, friend: *Let thy fountain be blessed.* The fountain here, friend, pictures the source of life and refreshment in marriage, the marriage relationship itself; and we are told, let it be blessed. God wants our marriages to be blessed, friend, to be a source of life and refreshment and joy; let thy fountain be blessed. This is God's desire for marriage, friend: not a dry and joyless thing, but a blessed fountain, a source of refreshment and delight.

See the call to keep rejoicing, friend: *and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.* God calls us to rejoice with the wife of our youth, friend; to keep delighting in the one we married, even as the years pass. The wife of thy youth, friend, is the one married in youth, the one we have grown old with; and we are called to keep rejoicing with her, to keep delighting in her, through all the years. This is a call, friend, to a lasting joy and delight in our spouse; not a joy that fades as youth fades, but a joy that continues, a rejoicing in the spouse of our youth even into old age.

How important this is for a lasting marriage, friend. It is easy, friend, for the joy and delight of early marriage to fade over the years; for husband and wife to grow used to one another, to take one another for granted, to lose the rejoicing they once had. But God calls us, friend, to keep rejoicing, to rejoice with the spouse of our youth, to keep delighting in one another through all the years. The marriages that stay sweet, friend, are the marriages that keep rejoicing; husband and wife continuing to delight in one another, even as they grow old together.

So let us keep rejoicing in our spouses, friend. Let us not let the joy and delight of our marriage fade, friend, growing used to one another, taking one another for granted. Let us keep delighting in one another, friend, rejoicing in the spouse of our youth, through all the years; let our marriage be a blessed fountain, a source of refreshment and joy, even into old age. Let us cultivate joy in our marriages, friend, taking time to delight in one another, to enjoy one another, to rejoice together. For God calls us, friend, to rejoice with the spouse of our youth; and a marriage that keeps rejoicing is a marriage that stays sweet, a blessed fountain through all the years. So let us keep our marriages joyful, friend; let us keep rejoicing in our spouses, delighting in them, enjoying them, through all of life. For this is God's call and God's gift, friend: to rejoice with the spouse of our youth, in a marriage that is a blessed fountain, joyful to the very end.`,
    prayer: `Lord, thank You for calling me to a lasting joy in my marriage: to let my fountain be blessed, and to rejoice with the spouse of my youth. Forgive me, Lord, for the times I have let the joy and delight of my marriage fade, growing used to my spouse, taking them for granted. Help me to keep rejoicing, Lord; to keep delighting in my spouse, to keep enjoying them, through all the years. Let my marriage be a blessed fountain, Lord, a source of refreshment and joy, even into old age. Help me to cultivate joy in my marriage, to take time to delight in my spouse, to rejoice together. Keep our marriage sweet and joyful, Lord, as we rejoice with the spouse of our youth all our days. In the name of Jesus Christ. Amen.`,
